3.text_en:
Section 3. In this Act:
'Immovable property' means land, or land with building or other construction thereon, or the construction which is the subject of the superficies right or the right of habitation;
'Commerce' means any activity related to the production of goods, trade, service, or any other commercial purpose;
'Industry' means any manufacturing activity using machinery or labor for the purpose of production, assembly, packing, or repair and maintenance of goods.

6.text_en:
Section 6. The immovable property leased under this Act must be located in one of the following areas:
(1) An area designated by the law on town and country planning for commercial or industrial purposes;
(2) An industrial estate zone established under the law on Industrial Estate Authority of Thailand.
